Looking back at the code, `_deserializeWithErrorWrapping` just calls `prop.deserialize(p, ctxt)` and wraps exceptions:

```java
protected final Object _deserializeWithErrorWrapping(JsonParser p,
        DeserializationContext ctxt, SettableBeanProperty prop)
    throws IOException
{
    try {
        return prop.deserialize(p, ctxt);
    } catch (Exception e) {
        wrapAndThrow(e, _beanType.getRawClass(), prop.getName(), ctxt);
        // never gets here, unless caller declines to throw an exception
        return null;
    }
}
```

So this change is functionally equivalent too. The real issue is deeper in the deserialization process.

